text: El Monte is a city in Los Angeles County, California. It is in the San Gabriel Valley, east of Los Angeles. At the 2020 census, 109,450 lived there. This was lower than the 2010 census, when 113,475 people lived there. The city was first incorporated in 1912. Its name means "the mountain" in Spanish. ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:Settlements in Los Angeles County, California Category:1912 establishments in California
